center|6\n|align=center|7\n|{{ya}}\n|Golden Ball\n|-\n!  scope=\"row\" data-sort-value=\"1982\" style=\"text-align: left;\"| {{flag|Spain}} [[1982 FIFA World Cup|1982]]\n| data-sort-value=\"Rossi, Paolo\" | [[Paolo Rossi]]\n|{{fb|ITA|1946}}\n|align=center|6\n|align=center|7\n|{{ya}}\n|Golden Ball\n|-\n!  scope=\"row\" data-sort-value=\"1986\" style=\"text-align: left;\"| {{flag|Mexico}} [[1986 FIFA World Cup|1986]]\n| data-sort-value=\"Lineker, Gary\" | [[Gary Lineker]]\n|{{fb|ENG}}\n|align=center|6\n|align=center|5\n|{{ya}}\n|\n|-\n!  scope=\"row\" data-sort-value=\"1990\" style=\"text-align: left;\"| {{flag|Italy|1946}} [[1990 FIFA World Cup|1990]]\n| data-sort-value=\"Schillaci, Salvatore\" | [[Salvatore Schillaci]]\n|{{fb|ITA|1946}}\n|align=center|6\n|align=center|7\n|{{ya}}\n|Golden Ball\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=2 data-sort-value=\"1994\" style=\"text-align: left;\"| {{flag|USA}} [[1994 FIFA World Cup|1994]]\n| data-sort-value=\"Stoichkov, Hristo\" | [[Hristo Stoichkov]]\n|{{fb|BUL}}\n| rowspan=\"2;\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|6\n|align=center|7\n|{{ya}}\n|Bronze Ball\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"Salenko, Oleg\" | [[Oleg Salenko]]\n|{{fb|RUS}}\n|align=center|3\n|{{na}}\n|\n|-\n!  scope=\"row\" data-sort-value=\"1998\" style=\"text-align: left;\"| {{flag|France}} [[1998 FIFA World Cup|1998]]\n| data-sort-value=\"Suker, Davor\" | [[Davor \u0160uker]]\n|{{fb|CRO}}\n|align=center|6\n|align=center|7\n|{{ya}}\n|Silver Ball\n|-\n!  scope=\"row\" data-sort-value=\"2002\" style=\"text-align: left;\"| {{flag|South Korea|1997}} and<br>{{flag|Japan}} [[2002 FIFA World Cup|2002]]\n| data-sort-value=\"Ronaldo\" | [[Ronaldo (Brazilian footballer)|Ronaldo]]\n|{{fb|BRA}}\n|align=center|8\n|align=center|7\n|{{ya}}\n|Silver Ball\n|-\n!  scope=\"row\" data-sort-value=\"2006\" style=\"text-align: left;\"| {{flag|Germany}} [[2006 FIFA World Cup|2006]]\n| data-sort-value=\"Klose, Miroslav\" | [[Miroslav Klose]]\n|{{fb|GER}}\n|align=center|5\n|align=center|7\n|{{ya}}\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=4 data-sort-value=\"2010\" style=\"text-align: left;\"| {{flag|South Africa}} [[2010 FIFA World Cup|2010]]\n| data-sort-value=\"Muller, Thomas\" | [[Thomas M\u00fcller]]\n|{{fb|GER}}\n| rowspan=\"4;\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|5\n|align=center|7\n|{{ya}}\n|Best Young Player\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"Villa, David\" | [[David Villa]]\n|{{fb|ESP}}\n|align=center|7\n|{{na}}\n|Silver Boot, Bronze Ball\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"Sneijder, Wesley\" | [[Wesley Sneijder]]\n|{{fb|NED}}\n|align=center|7\n|{{na}}\n|Bronze Boot, Silver Ball\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"Forlan, Diego\" | [[Diego Forl\u00e1n]]\n|{{fb|URU}}\n|align=center|7\n|{{na}}\n|Golden Ball\n|-\n!  scope=\"row\" data-sort-value=\"2014\" style=\"text-align: left;\"| {{flag|Brazil}} [[2014 FIFA World Cup|2014]]\n| data-sort-value=\"Rodriguez, James\" | [[James Rodr\u00edguez]]\n|{{fb|COL}}\n|align=center|6\n|align=center|5\n|{{ya}}\n|\n|-\n!  scope=\"row\" data-sort-value=\"2018\" style=\"text-align: left;\"| {{flag|Russia}} [[2018 FIFA World Cup|2018]]\n| data-sort-value=\"Kane, Harry\" | [[Harry Kane]] \n|{{fb|ENG}}\n|align=center|6\n|align=center|7\n|{{ya}}\n|\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of FIFA World Cup goalscorers]]\n*[[List of FIFA World Cup hat-tricks]]\n*[[List of FIFA World Cup own goals]]\n*[[All-time table of the FIFA World Cup]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=nb}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.fifa.com/tournaments/archive/worldcup/index.html FIFA World Cup statistics at FIFA.com]\n*[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesw/worldcup.html Statistics at RSSSF]\n*[http://www.planetworldcup.com/CUPS/tournaments.html Planet World Cup]\n{{FIFA World Cup}}\n\n{{featured list}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:List Of Fifa Men's World Cup Goalscorers}}\n[[Category:FIFA World Cup-related lists|Goalscorers]]\n[[Category:FIFA World Cup records and statistics]]\n", "text_old": "[[File:Brazil vs Germany, in Belo Horizonte 10.jpg|thumb|300px|Klose celebrating his record-breaking 16th World Cup goal|alt=refer to caption]]\nMore than 2,000 goals have been scored in the 21 editions of the [[FIFA World Cup|FIFA Men\u2019s World Cup]] final tournaments, not counting penalties scored during [[List of FIFA World Cup penalty shoot-outs|shoot-outs]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Second-half surge sees Tunisia bow out in style |url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/news/second-half-surge-sees-tunisia-bow-out-in-style |publisher=FIFA |accessdate=2018-07-09}}</ref> Since the first goal scored by [[France national football team|French]] player [[Lucien Laurent]] at the [[1930 FIFA World Cup]],<ref name=milestones>{{cite report|date=October 2007|url=https://www.fifa.com/mm/document/fifafacts/mcwc/ip-301_02a_fwc_goals_22689.pdf | title=FIFA World Cup \u2014 Milestone Goals|format=PDF|publisher=FIFA|page=1|accessdate=2014-09-05}}</ref> [[List of FIFA World Cup goalscorers|more than 1,250 footballers]] have scored goals in the Men\u2019s World Cup final tournaments,<ref name=worldfootball/> of whom just 97 have scored five or more.\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%; text-align:center; float: right; clear: right; margin: 0.5em 0 0.5em 1em;\"\n|+Numbers of goalscorers<ref name=worldfootball>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldfootball.net/alltime_goalgetter/wm/tore/ | title= World Cup \u2014 All-time Topscorers  | accessdate=2015-09-25 |work=WorldFootball.net | publisher=HEIM:SPIEL Medien GmbH & Co. KG }}</ref><ref name=FIFA-players>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/fifa-tournaments/statistics-and-records/worldcup/players/index.html | title=FIFA World Cup Players Statistics \u2014 Players with the Most Goals Scored| publisher=FIFA| accessdate=2018-05-15}}</ref><ref name=rsssf>{{cite web| url=http://www.rsssf.com/tables/30all-scor.html|title=World Cup 1930\u20132014 \u2014 Final Tournaments \u2014 Top-100 Goal Scorers|accessdate=2015-09-22|website=[[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation]]|first= Jaroslaw |last=Owsianski |date=2014-07-24}}</ref><!-- only up to 4 goals; Ademir is not updated--><!-- (including own goals scored for opponent)-->\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Goals !! scope=\"col\"|\u226511 !! scope=\"col\"|10 !! scope=\"col\"|9 !! scope=\"col\"|8 !! scope=\"col\"|7 !! scope=\"col\"|6 \n! scope=\"col\" style=\"border-right:1px solid;\"|5 !! scope=\"col\"|4 !! scope=\"col\"|3 !! scope=\"col\"|2 \n! scope=\"col\" style=\"border-right:1px solid;\"| 1  !! scope=\"col\"|Total\n|- style=\"border-bottom:1px solid;\"\n! scope=\"row\"|Nos. of players \n|7 ||6 ||9 ||7 ||8 ||26 ||style=\"border-right:1px solid;\"|34\n| >50<!-- 62 --> ||>90<!-- 99 --> ||>200<!--242--> ||style=\"border-right:1px solid;\"|>750<!--796-->\n|>1,250<!--1296-->\n|}\n[[File:Miroslav klose2.jpg|alt=Klose in black suit|thumb|[[Miroslav Klose]] is the player with the most goals, scoring 16.]]\nThe top goalscorer of the inaugural competition was [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]]'s [[Guillermo St\u00e1bile]] with eight goals. Since then, only 22 players have scored more at all the games played at the World Cup than St\u00e1bile did throughout the 1930 tournament. The first was [[Hungary national football team|Hungary]]'s [[S\u00e1ndor Kocsis]] with eleven [[1954 FIFA World Cup|in 1954]]. At the [[1958 FIFA World Cup|next tournament]], France's [[Just Fontaine]] improved on this record with 13 goals in only six games. [[Gerd M\u00fcller]] scored 10 for [[Germany national football team|West Germany]] [[1970 FIFA World Cup|in 1970]] and broke the overall record when he scored his 14th goal in the World Cup final tournament during West Germany's win in the [[1974 FIFA World Cup Final|1974 final]]. His record stood for more than three decades until [[Ronaldo (Brazilian footballer)|Ronaldo]]'s 15 goals between [[1998 FIFA World Cup|1998]] and [[2006 FIFA World Cup|2006]] for [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]]. Germany's [[Miroslav Klose]] went on to score a record 16 goals across four consecutive tournaments between [[2002 FIFA World Cup|2002]] and [[2014 FIFA World Cup|2014]]. Only two other players have surpassed 10 goals in the World Cup: [[Pel\u00e9]] with 12 between 1958 and 1970 for Brazil, and [[J\u00fcrgen Klinsmann]] with 11 between [[1990 FIFA World Cup|1990]] and 1998 for Germany.\n\nOf all the players who have played in the World Cup finals, only six have achieved an average of two goals or more per game played: Kocsis, Fontaine, St\u00e1bile, [[Russia national football team|Russia]]'s [[Oleg Salenko]], [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland]]'s [[Josef H\u00fcgi]], and [[Poland national football team|Poland]]'s [[Ernst Wilimowski]] \u2014 the last of these scored four in his [[Brazil v Poland (1938 FIFA World Cup)|single World Cup game]] in 1938.<ref name=goalscorers>{{cite web|url= https://www.fifa.com/fifa-tournaments/statistics-and-records/worldcup/players/index.html |title= FIFA World Cup Players Statistics |publisher=FIFA|date=2014-07-25 |accessdate=2014-07-30}}</ref> The top 97 goalscorers have represented 28 nations, with 14 players scoring for Brazil, and another 14 for Germany or West Germany. In total, 64 footballers came from [[UEFA]] (Europe), 29 from [[CONMEBOL]] (South America), and only four from elsewhere: [[Cameroon national football team|Cameroon]], [[Ghana national football team|Ghana]], [[Australia national soccer team|Australia]], and the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]].\n\nFontaine holds the record for the most goals scored at a single tournament, with 13 goals in 1958. The players that came closest were Kocsis in 1954, M\u00fcller in 1970 and [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]]'s [[Eus\u00e9bio]] [[1966 FIFA World Cup|in 1966]], with 11, 10 and 9, respectively. The lowest scoring top scorer was [[1962 FIFA World Cup|in 1962]], when six players tied at only four goals each. Across the 21 editions of the World Cup finals, 30 footballers have been credited with the most tournament goals, and no one has achieved this feat twice. Nine of them scored at least seven goals in a tournament, while Brazil's [[Jairzinho]] became the only footballer to score at least seven goals without being the top goalscorer of that tournament in 1970. These 30 top goalscorers played for 19 nations, the most (five) for Brazil. Another five came from other South American countries, with the remaining 20 coming from Europe. Excluding the [[2010 FIFA World Cup|2010 edition]], all the top tournament scorers won the [[World Cup Golden Boot|Golden Boot]].\n\n==Overall top goalscorers==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Table key\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |\u2666\n| Denotes national top scorers (or joint top scorers) at the World Cup\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |#\n| Denotes players still active at international level\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |[ ]\n| Denotes tournaments where the player was part of the squad, but did not play in a match\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |( )\n| Denotes tournaments where the player played in a match, but did not score a goal\n|}\n\n[[File:Wolfgang Overath, Gerd Muller 1974.jpg|thumb|Gerd M\u00fcller ''(right)'' scored 14 goals for West Germany.|alt=Gerd M\u00fcller with a World Cup in his hand]]\n[[File:Pel\u00e9 jump 1958.jpg|thumb|Pel\u00e9 ''(right)'' scored 12 goals for Brazil.|alt=Pele jumping for the ball]]\n[[File:Thomas M\u00fcller, Germany national football team (03).jpg|thumb|Thomas M\u00fcller has scored 10 goals for Germany.|alt=Thomas M\u00fcller standing on a field]]\n[[File:Bundesarchiv Bild 183-N0706-0040, Fu\u00dfball-WM, VR Polen - Brasilien 1-0.jpg|thumb|Grzegorz Lato ''(left)'' scored 10 goals for Poland.|alt=Grzegorz Lato is in the air]]\n[[File:Spain-Tahiti, Confederations Cup 2013 (18).jpg|thumb|David Villa ''(left)'' is the top World Cup goalscorer for Spain, with nine goals.|alt=David Villa walking on the field]]\n[[File:Valdomiro Vaz Franco, Roberto Rivelino, Jairzinho 1974.jpg|thumb|Jairzinho ''(upper right)'' and Roberto Rivellino ''(center)'' have scored nine and six goals, respectively, for Brazil.|alt=Four players talking to each other]]<!-- \n[[File:Johnny Rep 1974.jpg|thumb|Johnny Rep is the top World Cup goalscorer for the Netherlands, with 7 goals.]] -->\n<!-- [[File:NED-DEN Euro 2012 (10).jpg|thumb|Arjen Robben (orange, left) and Robin van Persie (orange, right) have scored 6 goals each for the Netherlands.]]\n[[File:Lothar Matth\u00e4us.jpg|thumb|Lothar Matth\u00e4us scored 6 goals in this record 25 matches at the World Cup.]]\n -->[[File:Landon Donovan corner kick.jpg|thumb|Landon Donovan is the first player from the United States to score five goals.|alt=Landon Donovan taking a corner kick]]\n<!-- [[File:Franz Beckenbauer 22-6-74.png|thumb|Franz Beckenbauer scored 5 goals for West Germany.]] -->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+Players with at least 5 goals at the FIFA World Cup tournaments<ref name=goalscorers/><ref name=database>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/fifa-tournaments/statistics-and-records/worldcup/index.html | title=FIFA World Cup All Time Statistics \u2014 All editions | publisher=FIFA| accessdate=2015-09-14}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" |Rank\n! scope=\"col\" |Player\n! scope=\"col\" |Team\n! scope=\"col\" |Goals<br>scored\n! scope=\"col\" |Matches<br>played\n! scope=\"col\" |{{Tooltip|Goals<br>per game<br>|Total number of goals scored divided by the total number of matches played}}{{refn|group=nb|Outside this list is [[Ernst Wilimowski]] of Poland, the player with the highest goals-to-games ratio in the World Cup. His ratio is 4.00 as he scored four goals in [[1938 FIFA World Cup final tournament#Brazil vs Poland|his only World Cup appearance]], in 1938.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.fifa.com/fifa-tournaments/news/y=2009/m=6/news=more-goals-than-caps-1065779.html|title=More goals than caps|date=2009-06-03|publisher=FIFA|access-date=2018-08-18|language=en-GB|quote= The Golden Shoe may have eluded Ernest Wilimowski, but he does boast the best goals-to-games ratio in World Cup history at 400 per cent. Indeed, in his solitary appearance \u2013 an unforgettable match at France 1938 \u2013 he scored four of Poland's goals in a 6-5 defeat by Brazil in the first round.|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180408010306/https://www.fifa.com/fifa-tournaments/news/y=2009/m=6/news=more-goals-than-caps-1065779.html|archive-date=2018-04-08}}</ref>}}\n! scope=\"col\" |Tournaments\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"|Notes\n|-\n| 1\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" data-sort-value=\"Klose, Miroslav\"|[[Miroslav Klose]]\n|align=left|{{fb|GER}}\n!scope=row| 16\n|24\n|{{Decimals|16/24|2}}\n|data-sort-value=\"2002-2006-2010-2014\"|2002, 2006, 2010, 2014\n|<small>[[List of international goals scored by Miroslav Klose|list]]</small><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldfootball/statisticsandrecords/players/player=182206/ |title=Miroslav Klose|publisher=FIFA|date=2014-07-25 |accessdate=2014-07-30}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" data-sort-value=\"Ronaldo\"| [[Ronaldo (Brazilian footballer)|Ronaldo]]\n|align=left|{{fb|BRA}}\n!scope=row| 15\n|19\n|{{Decimals|15/19|2}}\n|data-sort-value=\"1998-2002-2006\"|[1994], 1998, 2002, 2006\n|<small>[[List of international goals scored by Ronaldo#FIFA World Cup goals|list]]</small><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldfootball/statisticsandrecords/players/player=92699/ |title= Ronaldo |publisher=FIFA|date=2014-07-25 |accessdate=2014-07-30}}</ref>\n|-\n| 3\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" data-sort-value=\"Muller, Gerd\"| [[Gerd M\u00fcller]]\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" data-sort-value=\"Germany\"| {{fb|FRG}}\n!scope=row| 14\n|13\n|{{Decimals|14/13|2}}\n|data-sort-value=\"1970-1974\"|1970, 1974\n|<small>[[List of international goals scored by Gerd M\u00fcller|list]]</small><ref name=gmuller>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldfootball/statisticsandrecords/players/player=174790/ |title= Gerd Mueller |publisher=FIFA|date=2014-07-25 |accessdate=2014-07-30}}</ref>\n|-\n| 4\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" data-sort-value