07499.html|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131027051922/http://www.fifa.com/worldfootball/releases/newsid%3D107499.html|title=American Bert Patenaude credited with first hat trick in FIFA World Cup history|publisher=FIFA|date=2006-11-10|archivedate=2013-10-27|url-status=dead}}</ref>}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldfootball/statisticsandrecords/players/player=63829 |title= Leonidas |publisher=FIFA|date=2014-07-25 |accessdate=2014-07-30}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" data-sort-value=\"Ademir\"| [[Ademir Marques de Menezes|Ademir]]\n|align=left|{{fb|BRA|1889}}\n|6\n|{{Decimals|8/6|2}}\n|data-sort-value=\"1950\"|1950\n| <small>[[Ademir de Menezes#1950 World Cup statistics|list]]</small>{{refn|group=nb|There was a controversy regarding the number of goals scored by [[Ademir]] in 1950 because of incomplete data from the final group round game against [[Spain national football team|Spain]], that ended in a 6\u20131 victory for [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]]. The fifth Brazilian goal was credited to [[Jair]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/news/2005/aug/16/guardianobituaries.football | title = Obituary \u2014 Jair da Rosa Pinto | first=Brian |last=Glanville| newspaper=The Guardian| date = 2005-08-16| accessdate=2014-09-05}}</ref> but is now credited to Ademir.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/round=209/match=1186/index.html#nosticky |title=1950 FIFA World Cup Brazil \u2013 Brazil 6:1 Spain | publisher=FIFA|date=2014-07-25| accessdate=2014-07-30}}</ref>}}<ref name=ademir>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldfootball/statisticsandrecords/players/player=45005 |title=Ademir |publisher=FIFA|date=2014-07-25 |accessdate=2014-07-30}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" data-sort-value=\"Miguez, Oscar\"| [[\u00d3scar M\u00edguez]]<sup>\u2666</sup>\n|align=left|{{fb|URU}}\n|7\n|{{Decimals|8/7|2}}\n|data-sort-value=\"1950-1954\"|1950, 1954\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldfoot