eats Newton\n| page =14\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LXV| issue=20065\n| date = 1928-10-01\n| url = https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19281001.2.154.1\n| accessdate = 2019-10-04}}</ref>\n|| Ponsonby|| 8 || Newton || 5 || Carlaw Park # 1, 3pm \n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Final\n| 6 Oct <ref>{{cite news \n| title =Roope Rooster Final/Marist Defeats Ponsonby/A Margin of Two Points\n| page =14\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LXV| issue=20071\n| date = 1928-10-08\n| url = https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19281008.2.167.2\n| accessdate = 2019-10-04}}</ref>\n|| Marist|| 10 || Ponsonby || 8 || Carlaw Park # 1, 3pm\n|-\n|}\n\n===Stormont Memorial Shield===\n[[Marist Saints|Marist]] won the Stormont Shield for the first time when they defeated the Senior A Grade champions [[North Shore Albions|Devonport]] with a late try by 9 to 8.\n{| class=\"wikitable mw-collapsible\"\n|+ class=\"nowrap\" | Stormont Shield\n|-\n|\n! scope=\"col\" | Date\n! scope=\"col\" | \n! scope=\"col\" | Score\n! scope=\"col\" | \n! scope=\"col\" | Score\n! scope=\"col\" | Venue\n! scope=\"col\" | Attendance\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Stormont Shield\n| 13 Oct <ref>{{cite news \n| title =Close of the Season/Match for Stormont Shield/Marist Defeats Devonport\n| page =16\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LXV| issue=20077\n| date = 1928-10-15\n| url = https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19281015.2.148.1\n| accessdate = 2019-09-29}}</ref>\n|| Marist|| 9 || Devonport || 8 || Carlaw Park # 1, 3pm||4,000\n|-\n|}\n\n===Stallard Cup Knockout Competition===\nIn the first round of matches the referee (Mr. Hill) in the [[Otahuhu Leopards|Otahuhu]] v Kingsland game stopped play early and awarded the game to Kingsland due to the rough play of the [[Otahuhu Leopards|Otahuhu]] side. There were several fights during the match and the referee had difficulty keeping spectators off the field. According to the writer in the NZ Herald this \u201cwas not the first time the spectators at [[Otahuhu]] had made trouble, and they were really the cause of the players getting out of hand\u201d.<ref>{{cite news \n| title =Abrupt Termination/Rugby League Match/Result of Rough Play\n| page =11\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LXV| issue=20047\n| date = 1928-09-10\n| url = https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19280910.2.102\n| accessdate = 2019-10-04}}</ref>\n\nThe final saw Grafton and [[Point Chevalier Pirates|Point Chevalier]] tied at the end of normal time necessitating two extra periods of five minutes before Monaghan of [[Point Chevalier Pirates|Point Chevalier]] kicked a penalty goal to win the cup. This handed [[Point Chevalier Pirates|Point Chevalier]] their first ever senior trophy.\n{| class=\"wikitable mw-collapsible\"\n|+ class=\"nowrap\" | 1928 Stallard Cup Results\n|-\n|\n! scope=\"col\" | Date\n! scope=\"col\" | \n! scope=\"col\" | Score\n! scope=\"col\" | \n! scope=\"col\" | Score\n! scope=\"col\" | Venue\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Round 1\n| 8 Sep <ref>{{cite news \n| title =Roope Rooster Competition/First Series of Matches/Devonport\u2019s Narrow Victory\n| page =13\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LXV| issue=20047\n| date = 1928-09-10\n| url = https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19280910.2.132.1\n| accessdate = 2019-10-04}}</ref>\n|| Point Chevalier|| 15 || Mangere || 8 || Carlaw Park # 2, 1:45pm \n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | -\n| 8 Sep || Grafton || 10 || Northcote || 2 || Auckland Domain # 1, 3pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | -\n| 8 Sep || Otahuhu || 5 || Kingsland || 8 || Otahuhu, 3pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Semi Final\n| 22 Sep <ref>{{cite news \n| title = Roope Rooster Competition/Play in the Semi-Final/Marist Beats Devonport\n| page =14\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LXV| issue=20059\n| date = 1928-09-24\n| url = https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19280924.2.156.1\n| accessdate = 2019-10-04}}</ref>\n|| Point Chevalier|| 13 || Parnell || 6 || Point Chevalier,